# Render Deployment

## Project Architecture
Single Render Web Service (Docker) serving both the Go API and built Vite frontend.
- **Repo**: timlinquist/next_pitch_site
- **Deploy branch**: `render`
- **Service ID**: `srv-d65uhnrnv86c73e04mk0`
- **Workspace**: `tea-d65ttqsr85hc73d1uld0` (My Workspace)
- **Dockerfile**: multi-stage at project root (Node build → Go build → Alpine runtime)
- **Migrations**: run automatically on container startup via `./migrate -action up`

## Render CLI

Use `render` CLI for deployment tasks. Common commands:
- `render services list` — list services
- `render deploys list --service <service-id>` — list recent deploys
- `render logs --service <service-id>` — tail live logs
- `render deploys create --service <service-id>` — trigger manual deploy

When debugging build/deploy failures, use `render logs` or `render deploys list` to fetch logs directly rather than asking the user to paste them.

## Key Environment Variables on Render
- `PORT` — set automatically by Render
- `DATABASE_URL` — linked Render Postgres (internal URL)
- `AUTH0_DOMAIN` — just the domain, no `https://` prefix (e.g. `dev-cx0z71mw7lq3og41.us.auth0.com`)
- `VITE_AUTH0_CLIENT_DOMAIN`, `VITE_AUTH0_CLIENT_ID` — must have **Build** visibility (baked into JS at Docker build time)
- `AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID`, `AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY`, `AWS_S3_BUCKET`, `AWS_REGION`
- `SMTP_HOST`, `SMTP_PORT`, `SMTP_USERNAME`, `SMTP_PASSWORD`

## Relative Paths in Docker Container
Working directory is `/app/backend`. All paths are relative to that:
- Frontend dist: `../frontend/dist`
- Email templates: `templates/email/`
- DB migrations: `db/migrations/`
